    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect polar encoding in MCS selection path\n\n### Summary\nThe NR polar encoder was producing incorrect codewords due to wrong bit shift operations in the `encode_packed_byte` function. This caused degraded BLER performance and resulted in conservative MCS selection that didn't match the actual channel conditions or UE capabilities.\n\nThe issue was in `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrPolar_tools/nr_polar_procedures.c` where right shift operations were used instead of the correct left shift operations for polar encoding.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder normal operation, the incorrect encoding manifests as:\n- Higher than expected BLER at given SNR levels\n- MCS selection algorithm choosing lower MCS indices than optimal\n- Reduced throughput in good channel conditions\n\nThe issue becomes more pronounced when:\n1. Running NR DL transmission with polar-coded channels (PBCH, PDCCH, PDSCH with short blocks)\n2. Using high MCS indices where polar coding gain is critical\n3. In scenarios with good SNR where higher order modulations are selected\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrPolar_tools/nr_polar_procedures.c`: Corrected bit shift operations in `encode_packed_byte` function from right shifts to left shifts to match polar encoding specification.\n"
}